  "texts": [
    "The CS empirical type ranked second, with 60 papers (33.5%) using real-world datasets from hospitals or healthcare units.",
    "Among these papers, 46 were classified as SP studies, 12 as ER studies, and two as VR studies.",
    "By contrast, survey-based evaluations were relatively uncommon, with only two SP studies (1.1%) employing this method.",
    "It is worth noting that six papers used both public and real-life datasets and were hence double-counted in HBE and CS empirical types.",
    "Besides, 12 CS papers used real-world data from their previous works."
  ],
